This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a method for detecting 2D image objects using orientation patterns. The use of wavelet-type transforms and cross-correlations also suggests a focus on image processing and analysis. The paper also mentions the use of generalized linear regression, which could place it in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the identification of a curved geometry on the position-orientation domain suggests a focus on mathematical modeling and analysis, which could place it in the information theory (cs.IT), numerical analysis (cs.NA), or graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories.
